bib_record.title: Polarization effects in the C-12(3He,pp) reaction at 33 MeV.

free_txt: The reaction products were detected
in four delta E-E counter telescopes, each consisting
of a 100 mu-m surface-barrier detector and a 5 mm
Si(Li) detector. The data were taken in two different
arrangements of the telescopes inside the scattering
chamber.
No information about source of uncertainty
33.3 MeV polarized He-3 beam
Self-supporting 10 mg/cm2 carbon target was used.
Two telescopes were positioned symmetrically below and
above the horizontal plane, one pair to the left and
one to the right of the incident beam, keeping the
polar angle theta equal for all telescopes. Angle
definition: ANG is the polar angle between the He-2
cluster and He-3 beam direction. ANG-AZ is the angle
between the reaction planes.
